<!-- Campaign event template for standard USN-style "daily intentions message" (DIM) - formatting taken from real world examples -->

<ScrollViewer xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
  xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
  xmlns:local="clr-namespace:SeapowerUI">

	<Border HorizontalAlignment="Center" VerticalAlignment="Center" Width="900" TextElement.FontFamily="Courier New" TextElement.Foreground="Black" TextElement.FontSize="16" Padding="45">
		<Border.Effect>
			<DropShadowEffect />
		</Border.Effect>
		<Border.Background>
			<ImageBrush ImageSource="{Binding Assets[bkg_paper]}" Stretch="UniformToFill"/>
		</Border.Background>
		
        <StackPanel Orientation="Vertical">

		<Grid
		  xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
		  xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml" >
		<Grid.RowDefinitions>
			<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
		</Grid.RowDefinitions>
			<Grid.ColumnDefinitions>
				<ColumnDefinition Width="Auto"/>
				<ColumnDefinition Width="3*"/>
				<ColumnDefinition Width="Auto"/>
			</Grid.ColumnDefinitions>
			
			<TextBlock Grid.Row="0" Grid.Column="0" Text="NAVAL MESSAGE" Margin="0" FontFamily="Arial Narrow Bold" FontSize="26" FontWeight="Bold" TextAlignment="Left"/>
			<TextBlock Grid.Row="0" Grid.Column="1" Text="*******S E C R E T*******" Margin="40,0,40,0" FontWeight="Bold" TextAlignment="Center"/>
			<TextBlock Grid.Row="0" Grid.Column="2" Text="NAVY DEPARTMENT" Margin="0" FontFamily="Arial Narrow Bold" FontSize="26" FontWeight="Bold" TextAlignment="Right"/>
			
		</Grid>
		
		<Rectangle HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Height="1" Fill="Black" Margin="0,0,0,1"/>
		<Rectangle HorizontalAlignment="Stretch" Height="1" Fill="Black" Margin="0,0,0,10"/>

			<Grid
			  xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
			  xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml">
			<Grid.RowDefinitions>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="10"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
					<RowDefinition Height="Auto"/>
				</Grid.RowDefinitions>
				<Grid.ColumnDefinitions>
					<ColumnDefinition Width="Auto"/>
					<ColumnDefinition Width="10"/>
					<ColumnDefinition Width="*"/>
					<ColumnDefinition Width="Auto"/>
				</Grid.ColumnDefinitions>
				<TextBlock Grid.Row="1" Grid.ColumnSpan="4" HorizontalAlignment="Left" FontSize="16">
					IMMEDIATE<LineBreak/>
					O 082100Z AUG 85
				</TextBlock>
				
				<TextBlock Grid.Row="1" Grid.Column="3" FontSize="16" Text="ZYUW RUHGOAA0777 2202100"/>

				<TextBlock Grid.Row="3" Grid.Column="0" FontSize="16" Text="FM"/>
				<TextBlock Grid.Row="3" Grid.Column="2" FontSize="16" Text="CTF 77"/>
				<TextBlock Grid.Row="4" Grid.Column="0" FontSize="16" Text="TO"/>
				<TextBlock Grid.Row="4" Grid.Column="2" FontSize="16" Text="TF 77, CVW-9, NAVFAC DARWIN, 10 SQN RAAF"/>
				<TextBlock Grid.Row="11" Grid.Column="0" FontSize="16" Text="INFO"/>
				<TextBlock Grid.Row="11" Grid.Column="2" FontSize="16" Text="CINCPACFLT"/>
				<TextBlock Grid.Row="13" Grid.Column="0" FontSize="16" Text="SUBJ:"/>
				<TextBlock Grid.Row="13" Grid.Column="2" FontSize="16" Text="SITREP 09/1200Z - 10/1200Z - MSG NO 047/85"/>

				<TextBlock Grid.Row="15" Grid.ColumnSpan="4" FontSize="16" TextWrapping="Wrap">
					<LineBreak/>
					SECRET
					<LineBreak/>
					<LineBreak/>
					1. (S) STRATEGIC SITUATION: U.S. and Allied forces have consolidated at Darwin after the fall of Singapore and Malaysia. Enemy forces continue to drive southeast, and intel suspects their goal is to fully isolate the Allied forces embattled on Luzon, forcing a settlement. The neutralization of Sumatra and Java by the enemy now allows him full access to the Indian Ocean, from where USSR forces can threaten the Persian Gulf, western Australia, and South Africa. Soviet naval air units enjoy freedom of operation from Vladivostok south to Cam Ranh Bay, and their submarines have been reported entering the Timor Sea.
					<LineBreak/>
				</TextBlock>
				<TextBlock Grid.Row="16" Grid.ColumnSpan="4" FontSize="16" TextWrapping="Wrap">
					2. (S) MISSION: TF 77 will conduct defense of Australia mission in concert with Allied forces at Darwin with CTF 77 in overall command.
					<LineBreak/>
				</TextBlock>
				<TextBlock Grid.Row="17" Grid.ColumnSpan="4" TextWrapping="Wrap">
					3. (S) TF 77 STATUS:
				</TextBlock>	
				<TextBlock Grid.Row="18" Grid.ColumnSpan="4" TextWrapping="Wrap" Margin="20,0,0,0">	
					- KITTY HAWK remains at Puget Sound for repairs after mine strike at Yokosuka.
					<LineBreak/>
					- Elements of CVW-9 operating shore-based from Darwin.
					<LineBreak/>
					- MOOSBRUGGER detached to urgent duty at Cooktown at request of Australian government.
					<LineBreak/>
					- VAW-114 Hawkeye lost over East Timor 07AUG. Replacement inbound from CVW-14 ETA 14AUG.
					<LineBreak/>
				</TextBlock>				
				<TextBlock Grid.Row="19" Grid.ColumnSpan="4" TextWrapping="Wrap">
					4. (S) ALLIED FORCES:
				</TextBlock>
				<TextBlock Grid.Row="20" Grid.ColumnSpan="4" TextWrapping="Wrap" Margin="20,0,0,0">
					- Australia: RAAF F-111 force badly attrited in interdiction strikes against enemy forces staging in Indonesia. RAAF JORN OTH search radar disabled 03AUG by enemy agents.
					<LineBreak/>
					- Malaysia/Indonesia: Friendly forces are scattered or have surrendered. No organized resistance expected from these forces.
					<LineBreak/>
					- Singapore: Complete rout led to total loss of RN Force F. Other British forces are fully tasked in Atlantic and Med.
					<LineBreak/>
				</TextBlock>
				<TextBlock Grid.Row="21" Grid.ColumnSpan="4" TextWrapping="Wrap">
					5. (S) INTEL / THREAT:
				</TextBlock>
				<TextBlock Grid.Row="22" Grid.ColumnSpan="4" TextWrapping="Wrap" Margin="20,0,0,0">
					- Australian coastwatchers were clandestinely inserted into Indonesia to monitor movement through critical chokepoints (Sunda, Lombok, Ombai/Wetar).
					<LineBreak/>
					- Increased Bear-D activity over Timor and Arafura Seas indicates possible enemy sortie in our direction in next 48-72 hours. VF-111 reports one shootdown and one Bear-D escaped 08AUG.
					<LineBreak/>
					- SIGINT indicates enemy submarines beginning transit south.
					<LineBreak/>
				</TextBlock>	
				<TextBlock Grid.Row="23" Grid.ColumnSpan="4" TextWrapping="Wrap">
					6. (S) REMARKS: This is a critical tipping point in the campaign against the enemy. We have been pushed back farther than any pre-war estimate would have anticipated, but with proper coordination we can stop the enemy cold here. Good luck and good hunting. CTF 77 sends.
					<LineBreak/>
				</TextBlock>
				<TextBlock Grid.Row="24" Grid.ColumnSpan="4" TextWrapping="Wrap">
					SIGNED: CAPT C. F. ROBINSON
					<LineBreak/>
					CTF 77
					<LineBreak/>
					<LineBreak/>
					SECRET
					<LineBreak/>
					DO NOT DECLASSIFY WITHOUT APPROVAL OF ADDRESSEE
				</TextBlock>
			</Grid>
        </StackPanel>
    </Border>
</ScrollViewer>
